request.description:
This is the initial Call, Parameters "key", "text"
Key comes from the account on NERD, text is the text that we want to analyze.
Returns "idDocument" that we use on next calls.

urlencoded.value: combined, alchemyapi, dandelionapi, dbspotlight, lupedia, opencalais, saplo, semitags, textrazor, thd, wikimeta, yahoo, zemanta

request.description:
This is the Second Call, Parameters "key", "idDocument" and "extractor"
"key" comes from the account on NERD, "idDocument" is what we receive from the initial call, document uploaded on server its give back us "idDocument" of that document that we want to analyze. "extractor" is important parameter so NERD is linked with many extractors. The accepted values are: {combined, alchemyapi, dandelionapi, dbspotlight, lupedia, opencalais, saplo, semitags, textrazor, thd, wikimeta, yahoo, zemanta}.
We tested is with "combined" and "textrazor"
Returns "idAnnotation" that we use on next calls.

This is the Last Call, Parameters "key", "idAnnotation" and "granularity"
"key" comes from the account on NERD, "idAnnotation" is what we receive from previous call. For "granularity" Accepted values: "oen" or "oed". The oen (One Entity per Name) reads all the entities found in the document. The oed (One Entity per Document) removes duplicates (a duplicate happens when two or more entities have the same NE,type and URI) and reads only one occurrence.

Returns json for the linked entities.
